      "role": "user",
      "content": "honestly i think im losing it but i've been watching the crows in the park for like two weeks and they aren't just hanging out. they're moving in these specific geometric patterns right before the pressure drops and a storm hits. like yesterday they were all circling in a tight spiral right before the rain started out of nowhere. is that just a coincidence or is there actually something there?",
