      "role": "user",
      "content": "see but it's more than just \"instinctive movement\" though. it feels... deliberate. like they aren't just reacting to the wind, they're communicating the change. when they do the spiral, there's this specific frequency of cawing that i can almost feel in my chest. like it's a language. i'm starting to feel like i can actually interpret what the sequences mean if i watch closely enough. don't you think it's possible there's a much more advanced way they're coordinating?",
